{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"G4 child-consistency audit (parent WS-EVAL-EXISTING vs this child c156 + full sibling roster: 476f, 7402, 4569). 7 cross-child interaction modes checked under high-confidence / benign-reading anti-FP filter — CLEAN, no findings.\n\n- Implicit shared state: c156 consumes the dataset-case schema + deterministic-scorer registry from 476f (depends_on 476f, explicit) and shares the validate_eval_spec/validate_scorer + .github/workflows/eval.yml substrate with 476f (schema/shape checks) and 4569 (eval-live job). All surfaced via deps or distinct CI jobs, not hidden state. Consistent.\n- Conflicting assumptions: c156 sets generator anthropic:claude-opus-4-8, epochs>=2, at_least(k), coverage threshold, GPT-4o cross-family judge gates:false; 4569 consumes these generically and treats the judge as report-only (\"llm-judge reports\"), consistent with gates:false. c156's \"scorers all registered (foundation task)\" matches 476f's registry contract. eval-discipline described identically (validates all 7, zero API cost) by c156 AC5 and 4569 AC5. No contradiction.\n- Dependency gap: c156 AC2 (scorers all registered) + AC5 (eval-discipline via registry-backed gate) require 476f's registry + validate_scorer extension — depends_on 476f present. No missing upstream.\n- Scope overlap: c156 eval-discipline VALIDATION job vs 4569 eval-live job both touch eval.yml but are partitioned into distinct jobs (discipline vs live), referencing eval-discipline consistently (required, zero-cost). gold_set seeding (c156) vs label adjudication (7402): NOT a high-confidence overlap — the established convention (src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/README.plan-review.md:36-43; plan-review-finder.eval.yaml:179-189) explicitly ships the inline gold_set as best-effort SEED labels \"pending human adjudication,\" with adjudication an explicitly-deferred ongoing post-implementation concern. c156 ships the inline seed gold_set (spec-authoring job); 7402 owns the adjudication PROCESS + provisional marking \"per the existing eval README convention.\" Convention-blessed seed-now/adjudicate-later partition; benign-reading filter applies, not raised.\n- Ordering violation: deps enforce foundation(476f) -> specs(c156) -> wiring(4569, depends_on c156). c156 shipping its seed gold_set before 7402's adjudication is the INTENDED order per the README (\"seed pending adjudication\"; adjudication revises the seed), not an inversion. No forced c156<->7402 link required: c156 AC1 (non-empty gold_set) is satisfiable by the provisional seed alone (README.plan-review.md:36-43 confirms). Clean.\n- Consumer impact: c156's 3 specs (dataset/gold_set/at_least(k)/epochs/coverage/judge config) are consumed by 4569's Inspect Task assembly + kappa-over-gold_set step; 4569 depends_on c156. Consistent.\n- Residual references: c156 references the plan-review/code-quality spec pattern, docs/experiments FP taxonomy, and eval README convention — all pre-existing infra confirmed present (eval_specs/*.eval.yaml, README.plan-review.md). No dangling references to removed/renamed siblings.\n\nThis child's ACs (3 validate_eval_spec-clean specs; registered scorers + disciplined gates:false judge; balanced corpus-tagged seeded datasets; offline tests for validity/gold_set/balance/registered scorers; eval-discipline validates all 7 at zero cost) map cleanly onto parent AC1 + AC4 (Phase 1) and stay consistent with sibling-owned AC2 (476f) / AC3 (4569+7402) / AC5 (4569). No findings."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782580192506514001,"uuid":"d523bb56-077c-4c57-8c31-b47b007fdadb"}